<p>I have two objects Maths and Science. I'm trying to add some modules based on the courses. For example if I add Core Algebra it should bind to Maths Object. So I can display all the Maths modules under Maths heading and Science modules under Science heading dynamically. At the moment module.name just displays the all the modules but doesn't bind to either of them.</p>  <pre><code>  = link_to 'Science', modules_path   = link_to 'Maths', modules_path  - @modules.each do |module|   %li     = link_to module.name  = link_to 'Add', new_module_path, class: 'btn btn-info' </code></pre>  <p>I added the following in the database so I have two at the moment. Similarly I want to add them from the browser.</p>  <pre><code>Science.find_or_create_by_name "Cell and molecular Biology" Maths.find_or_create_by_name "Core Algebra" </code></pre>  <p>Modules controller:</p>  <pre><code>Class ModulesController &lt; ApplicationController   def index     @modules = Module.all   end    def new     @module = Module.new   end    def create     @module = Module.new(params[:module])     if @module.save       redirect_to modules_path     else       render :new     end   end end </code></pre>  <p>Models:</p>  <pre><code>class Module &lt; ActiveRecord::Base   attr_accessible :name    def science?     self.is_a? Science   end    def maths?     self.is_a? Maths   end end  class Science &lt; Module; end class Maths &lt; Module; end </code></pre>